<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum left at the Department of State by
                                    Baron von Sternburg.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">German Embassy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-23"><hi rend="italic">August 23, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The Chinese minister in Berlin has been informed that the German
                                Government can not enter into any negotiations with Li Hung Chang
                                because it is not clear from whom he has received his credentials
                                and what credentials he holds as to negotiations with the
                                powers.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>